            <thetext>Since upgrading from v0.7 to v0.9 of opengrok the Home link near the top left of the browser does not work. Rather than taking me back to a fresh search panel, it simply returns the current web page.

For example, when a search takes me to the page:

http://sou-opengrok.eng.vmware.com:8080/search?q=blah

the Home link also points to:

http://sou-opengrok.eng.vmware.com:8080/search?q=blah</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>77795</commentid>
            <who name="Knut Anders Hatlen">knut.hatlen</who>
            <bug_when>2010-09-21 10:04:51 +0000</bug_when>
            <thetext>The home link is generated by calling HttpServletRequest.getContextPath(), which returns &quot;&quot; if the servlet is in the root directory. From the javadoc:

http://download.oracle.com/javaee/6/api/javax/servlet/http/HttpServletRequest.html#getContextPath%28%29
The path starts with a &quot;/&quot; character but does not end with a &quot;/&quot; character. For servlets in the default (root) context, this method returns &quot;&quot;.

I suppose we could fix that by always adding a trailing &quot;/&quot; character to the home link.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
